WEBVTT

00:00.090 --> 00:01.491
<i>Previously on "Heartland":</i>

00:01.534 --> 00:03.201
I can't seem to make ends meet!

00:03.235 --> 00:05.036
So when Caleb told me
about this prize money,

00:05.304 --> 00:06.704
<i>I knew I had to try.</i>

00:06.772 --> 00:08.273
I just can't believe you didn't
talk to me about it first.

00:08.307 --> 00:09.274
This is my money!

00:09.308 --> 00:10.675
It's our future!

00:10.742 --> 00:13.278
Lou, can I have a friend over
after school tomorrow?

00:13.312 --> 00:14.479
Yeah, sure, what's her name?

00:14.513 --> 00:15.813
His name is Stephen.

00:15.847 --> 00:18.550
Amy, would you consider
coming back to Hillhurst?

00:18.617 --> 00:20.251
Only this time
as my head trainer?

00:20.319 --> 00:22.187
- Are you serious?
- Very.

00:22.221 --> 00:23.455
I've been around
long enough to know

00:23.522 --> 00:24.922
that when Ahmed looks at you,

00:24.990 --> 00:27.559
it's with more
than professional admiration.

00:27.593 --> 00:28.726
Lou, that's crazy!

00:28.760 --> 00:31.062
I've been thinking a lot
about Charger,

00:31.096 --> 00:32.662
and I'd like to take
a look at him,

00:32.698 --> 00:35.032
see if there's anything
that I can do to help.

00:35.067 --> 00:36.266
Okay, well, what about us?

00:36.301 --> 00:37.635
One thing at a time.

00:43.709 --> 00:46.143
<i>Amy, wait! Listen to me!</i>

00:46.177 --> 00:49.513
Now, Ty goes and makes the most
ridiculous gamble in the world

00:49.547 --> 00:51.547
and you're gonna waste
your valuable time

00:51.582 --> 00:53.817
trying to help out him
and his stupid partner

00:53.851 --> 00:54.818
over a lost cause?!

00:54.852 --> 00:55.952
I've gotta do something.

00:55.987 --> 00:57.887
I can't just let Ty
throw his money away!

00:57.922 --> 00:59.555
But you've got
a perfectly good job, honey.

00:59.590 --> 01:01.891
Are you willing to--
Go, answer it.

01:01.926 --> 01:03.159
Ahmed, hey.

01:03.193 --> 01:05.194
Yes, um... I'm gonna be
a little bit late,

01:05.229 --> 01:07.163
but I will be there.

01:07.197 --> 01:08.697
There's just something
that I have to take care of.

01:08.732 --> 01:10.666
I'm really sorry.

01:10.734 --> 01:12.968
Okay. Absolutely.
Bye.

01:13.003 --> 01:14.603
There it is right there.
The prince.

01:14.638 --> 01:15.704
He's gonna lose patience
with you

01:15.772 --> 01:17.172
and then the cheques
are gonna stop.

01:17.206 --> 01:19.374
Dad, I can do my job
and help Ty, okay?

01:19.408 --> 01:20.643
Besides, it's really
not your business

01:20.677 --> 01:21.644
what's my business!

01:22.679 --> 01:25.881
I'm just trying...
Answer it.

01:25.915 --> 01:26.982
Ty, hey.

01:27.017 --> 01:29.383
Yeah, no, I'm-
I'm on my way, okay.

01:29.451 --> 01:30.985
I'll be there.
Bye!

01:33.856 --> 01:37.391
So Caleb...
Still trying to find a rider?

01:37.425 --> 01:39.560
I don't think there's
a barrel racer in Alberta

01:39.594 --> 01:41.595
you haven't texted.

01:41.630 --> 01:44.632
Face it,
that guy doesn't have it in him.

01:44.700 --> 01:47.101
He's all speed and no reward.

01:47.169 --> 01:49.236
But, hey, good luck with that.

01:54.276 --> 01:56.843
She drives me crazy.

01:56.878 --> 01:57.844
Well, I guess the word's out

01:57.879 --> 01:59.946
Charger's a non-starter.

02:00.014 --> 02:01.915
So what if he's an underdog?

02:01.983 --> 02:04.385
There's a reason people love
underdog stories so much.

02:04.452 --> 02:06.620
They always have happy endings.

02:06.688 --> 02:08.420
Caleb, how are we gonna
make this work?

02:08.455 --> 02:12.258
Just relax.
It's not over 'til it's over.

02:12.326 --> 02:13.693
Where's Amy?

02:14.795 --> 02:17.029
Jack, look at this
trick saddle!

02:19.166 --> 02:20.633
This is the one I want!

02:20.701 --> 02:21.634
Isn't it cool?

02:21.702 --> 02:23.336
<i>Yes, it is.</i>

02:23.370 --> 02:24.837
<i>Now I just have to figure
out how I'm gonna pay for it.</i>

02:24.905 --> 02:26.306
Well...

02:26.373 --> 02:29.374
What's the deal with you?

02:29.442 --> 02:31.543
Are you wearing perfume?!

02:31.611 --> 02:33.978
Okay, the deal is,
I have a lunch date.

02:34.013 --> 02:35.280
Lisa is coming over.

02:39.485 --> 02:41.386
Hello?

02:41.454 --> 02:44.423
Yes, she is.
Just hold on.

02:44.490 --> 02:45.824
Stephen.

02:47.259 --> 02:48.492
Hi!

02:49.762 --> 02:50.962
Yeah, I can meet you.

02:50.996 --> 02:54.498
I have to wait until Lou
and my dad get home.

02:55.601 --> 02:58.203
Actually,
they're here right now.

02:58.270 --> 02:59.938
Can I call you back?

03:00.005 --> 03:00.972
Okay. Bye.

03:02.074 --> 03:03.141
Um...

03:03.209 --> 03:04.876
Stephen wants to meet me
at Maggie's.

03:04.944 --> 03:07.277
Can someone give me a ride?

03:07.345 --> 03:08.278
Honey?

03:08.346 --> 03:10.080
Yeah, sure.
Let's go.

03:10.115 --> 03:11.081
I'm here.

03:11.116 --> 03:12.249
And the only reason I am

03:12.283 --> 03:13.316
is because I can't stand
the thought of Ty

03:13.351 --> 03:14.351
losing all
his hard-earned money,

03:14.385 --> 03:15.352
thanks to you!

03:15.386 --> 03:16.754
I know, I know.

03:16.788 --> 03:18.321
But he's a great horse,
you'll see!

03:18.356 --> 03:19.322
And all we have to do
is get a handle

03:19.390 --> 03:20.758
on his one little problem.

03:20.792 --> 03:22.559
I promise we won't take much
of your time at all.

03:22.627 --> 03:23.593
Okay, good,

03:23.661 --> 03:24.628
because Ahmed's already
called me

03:24.662 --> 03:26.662
a few times this morning,
wondering where I am!

03:26.696 --> 03:28.164
Aww! Poor little
needy prince!

03:28.198 --> 03:30.699
Caleb,
let's just get this done!

